Step 1: Identify the necessary values.  
• The inventory at the beginning is 0 (as of 2023-12-31) and at the end is 7,869,940 (as of 2024-02-03).  
• Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) from the income statement is 504,930.

Step 2: Calculate the average inventory.  
Average Inventory = (Beginning Inventory + Ending Inventory) / 2  
  = (0 + 7,869,940) / 2  
  = 3,934,970

Step 3: Calculate the Inventory Turnover Ratio.  
Inventory Turnover Ratio = COGS / Average Inventory  
  = 504,930 / 3,934,970  
  ≈ 0.1283  
Rounded to two decimal places, the ratio is approximately 0.13.

Thus, the solution in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Inventory Turnover Ratio": "0.13"}}
